You have several addons failing to load.  one is RasterPropMonitor.  B9 needs that to run properly, iirc.  Based on a quick look, I would take a hard look at the failing mods and see if they are out of date/corrupted.  Also, B9 was last updated for version 1.8.x, and you are running 1.12.2.  the mod is mainly parts, but some portions can break if the dependencies fail.  Take a look starting at line 592 in the log and go from there.
I was able to find the solution myself. Seemed to be Sandbox from WBI. For some reason that caused B9 to shoot off errors. What that interaction is, I have no idea.
